HT|B|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|The decision of "3 over 2" is actually pretty easy. If you know the opponents have an 8-card fit, you should not let them play there, pretty much never at the 2 level. If you do, at best you can hope for an average result and often you will get a below average result.|
PG| ***** 25 ***** |


AT|

If you know the opponents have an 8 card fit and have stopped at 2, you must bid 3 over 2. If you do not know they have an 8 card fit, then you don't have to bid. For example, in the typical 2 over 1 auction of|
