AT|
One is |cp|8|at|double;|cp||at| the other is a |cp|8|at|cue bid|cp||at| of their suit.|
PG| ***** 60 ***** |


AT|

Double as you all know is negative, showing the unbid major. |
PG| ***** 61 ***** |


AT|

A cue bid is a limit+ raise of partner's suit. With minor differences the criteria for cue bid are the same for majors and minors.|
PG| ***** 62 ***** |


AT|

Because a cue bid is a strong bid, now a jump raise is a weak bid.|
